<h1>Terms and Conditions/Privacy Policy</h1>

<h3>Arlington Public Library SMS Alerts Service Description</h3>
<p>The SMS Alerts service gives you the option to receive text messages from
	Arlington Public Library on your mobile device. After you opt into SMS Alerts,
	Arlington Public Library will send you library notices via text messages when you have overdue items, holds ready for pickup, etc. Contact the library for specific information about when you'll receive alerts.</p>
<p>You can choose to opt out of the SMS Alerts service at any time.</p>
<h3>Pricing: Message and data rates may apply. </h3>
<h3>Short Code Information</h3>
<p>All
	Arlington Public Library Alert services are originated from short codes 82453 or 35143. You will never receive any content from
	Arlington Public Library from any other source.</p>
<h3>Service/Help info</h3>
<p>To get help with the
	Arlington Public Library SMS Alert text message service, you may email us at
	smshelp@marmot.org.</p>
<p>You can also request our contact information from your mobile phone at any time by sending a text message with the word <strong>HELP</strong> to 82453 or 35143</p>
<h3>Opt In/Opt-Out info</h3>
<p>To opt out from the
	Arlington Public Library Alerts, send a text message with the word <strong>STOP, STOP ALL, END, QUIT, CANCEL</strong> or <strong>UNSUBSCRIBE</strong> to 82453 or 35143 from your mobile phone and we will unsubscribe you from our service. You will not receive any additional text messages via your mobile phone.</p>
<p>You may also opt out by logging into your patron record and updating your patron record.</p>
<h3>Frequency of program service</h3>
<p>
	Arlington Public Library Alert is a monthly subscription service.
	Arlington Public Library will send SMS alerts whenever you have new items that have become available for you to pick up. Message frequency is based on profile. Although
	Arlington Public Library does not charge for this service, message and data rates may apply.</p>
